### Instructions ###


----------------------------------------------------
* Install packages

- Install manually java-7-openjdk-amd64 and some packages: build-essentials, node v5.6.0, node-gyp v3.2.1, ant

To install build-essential package, type:

sudo apt-get install build-essential

After download node version 5.6.0 <https://nodejs.org/en/download/>, extract it on /opt/ folder or install by terminal, type: 

Node.js:

sudo apt-get install nodejs

Node package manager:

sudo apt-get install npm

Create a symbolic link for node:

sudo ln -s /usr/bin/nodejs /usr/bin/node

Install ant:

sudo apt-get install ant

./configure
sudo make
sudo make install

The next step is install node-gyp. Type: <https://github.com/nodejs/node-gyp>

npm install -g node-gyp

- Check if your jdk is installed on /usr/lib/jvm/java-7-openjdk-amd64 folder. If its is not there, you can modify on makefile the correct path on JNI variable or install from terminal the packages:

sudo apt-get install openjdk-7-jdk openjdk-7-jre
